The patient reports frequent auditory hallucinations and olfatory hallucinations without paranoid content or delusions. These hallucinations are reported after the TBI episode. The subject is fully functional both in his profession and socially. Given the objective measure of memory deficits without meaningful impairment in activities, the subject is being diagnosed as MCI.
